{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DevicePadProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DeviceProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3Gdk14DeviceProtocolP","text":"DeviceProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It allows querying the features provided by the pad device."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tablet pads may contain one or more groups, each containing a subset"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the buttons\/rings\/strips available. [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.DevicePad.get_n_groups"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be used to obtain the number of groups, [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.DevicePad.get_n_features"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.DevicePad.get_feature_group"},{"type":"text","text":"] can be combined to find out"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the number of buttons\/rings\/strips the device has, and how are they grouped."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each of those groups have different modes, which may be used to map each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"individual pad feature to multiple actions. Only one mode is effective"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(current) for each given group, different groups may have different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current modes. The number of available modes in a group can be found"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out through [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.DevicePad.get_group_n_modes"},{"type":"text","text":"], and the current mode"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for a given group will be notified through events of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDK_PAD_GROUP_MODE"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DevicePadProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkDevicePad"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DevicePad"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DevicePadRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gdk\/devicepadprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DeviceProtocol","doc:\/\/Gdk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gdk\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DevicePad","doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DevicePadRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DevicePadProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkDevicePad"},{"type":"t